The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) from databases with storage constraints, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed algorithm is iterative and involves assigning sub-messages to databases, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The convergence analysis of the algorithm involves concepts from control theory (cs.CC).
